.TH EODINGA 1 "2026-04-23" "eodinga 0.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
eodinga \- local-first instant file search for Windows and Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B eodinga
[\fB\-\-log-level\fR \fILEVEL\fR]
[\fB\-\-config\fR \fIPATH\fR]
[\fB\-\-db\fR \fIPATH\fR]
\fICOMMAND\fR
[\fIARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBeodinga\fR indexes filenames, paths, and supported document text on-device and exposes the same lexical search engine through CLI, GUI, and hotkey launcher surfaces.
The runtime is local-only: indexed roots are treated as read-only inputs and runtime writes stay inside the application config and database directories.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show the top-level help message and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-log-level \fILEVEL\fR
Set the runtime log level for the invoked command.
.TP
.B \-\-config \fIPATH\fR
Override the default configuration file path.
.TP
.B \-\-db \fIPATH\fR
Override the default SQLite index database path.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B index
Build or rebuild the on-disk index.
Supports \fB\-\-root\fR \fIPATH\fR to add one or more roots for the command and \fB\-\-rebuild\fR for a cold staged rebuild.
.TP
.B watch
Consume filesystem notifications and apply incremental updates to the existing index.
Use after a successful build when you want live updates outside the GUI-managed flow.
.TP
.B search
Execute one query from the shared DSL and print ranked hits.
Supports \fB\-\-json\fR, \fB\-\-limit\fR \fIN\fR, and \fB\-\-root\fR \fIPATH\fR.
.TP
.B stats
Print persisted index metadata and runtime counters.
Use \fB\-\-json\fR for machine-readable observability output.
.TP
.B gui
Launch the Qt application surface.
Supports \fB\-\-test-mode\fR for offscreen smoke validation.
.TP
.B doctor
Run local diagnostics covering dependencies, writable state paths, configured roots, and the active database path.
.TP
.B version
Print the packaged application version.
.SH QUERY EXAMPLES
.TP
.B eodinga search 'ext:pdf invoice'
Search PDF files matching the lexical term \fBinvoice\fR.
.TP
.B eodinga search 'date:this-week path:docs'
Limit results to recently modified files under paths containing \fBdocs\fR.
.TP
.B eodinga search 'regex:/todo|fixme/i' \-\-json
Run a case-insensitive regex query and print JSON results.
.TP
.B eodinga search 'is:duplicate size:>10M'
Find large duplicate candidates.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/eodinga/config.toml
Default Linux configuration path.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/eodinga/index.db
Default Linux SQLite index path.
.TP
.I %APPDATA%\\eodinga\\config.toml
Default Windows configuration path.
.TP
.I %LOCALAPPDATA%\\eodinga\\index.db
Default Windows SQLite index path.
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
Run \fBeodinga doctor\fR first when results look stale or the packaged surface behaves unexpectedly.
Run \fBeodinga stats --json\fR to confirm the active database path and counters.
Use \fBeodinga index --rebuild\fR when a clean staged rebuild is safer than waiting for live updates.
